Experimental Elixir	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Artificer Class Feature.Class Feature.Alchemist.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Whenever you finish a Long Rest while holding Alchemist's Supplies, you can use that tool to magically produce two elixirs. For each elixir, roll on the Experimental Elixir table for the elixir's effect, which is triggered when someone drinks the elixir. The elixir appears in a vial, and the vial vanishes when the elixir is drunk or poured out. If any elixir remains when you finish a Long Rest, the elixir and its vial vanish. &nl; Drinking an Elixir. As a Bonus Action, a creature can drink the elixir or administer it to another creature within 5 feet of itself. &nl; Creating Additional Elixirs. As a Magic action while holding Alchemist's Supplies, you can expend one spell slot to create another elixir. When you do so, you choose its effect from the Experimental Elixir table rather than rolling. &nl; When you reach certain Artificer levels, you can make an additional elixir at the end of each Long Rest: a total of three at level 5, four at level 9, and 5 at level 15. &nl; EXPERIMENTAL ELIXIR &nl;&nl; D6   Effect &nl; 1    Healing. The drinker regains a number of Hit Points equal to 2d8 plus your Intelligence modifier. &nl; 2    Swiftness. The drinker's Speed increases by 10 feet for 1 hour. &nl; 3    Resilience. The drinker gains a +1 bonus to AC for 10 minutes. &nl; 4    Boldness. The drinker can roll 1d4 and add the number rolled to every attack roll and saving throw they make for the next minute. &nl; 5    Flight. The drinker gains a Fly Speed of 10 feet for 10 minutes. &nl; 6    You determine the elixir's effect by choosing one of the other rows in this table.	KEY:Alchemist ~ Experimental Elixir	DESC:Number of elixir: %1|ExperimentalElixirTimes			DEFINE:ExperimentalElixirTimes|0					BONUS:VAR|ExperimentalElixirTimes|3+(ArtificerLVL>=9)+(ArtificerLVL>=15)																	SORTKEY:Class_Artificer_01d1c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Alchemical Savant	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Artificer Class Feature.Class Feature.Alchemist.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Whenever you cast a spell using your Alchemist's Supplies as the Spellcasting Focus, you gain a bonus to one roll of the spell. That roll must restore Hit Points or be a damage roll that deals Acid, Fire, Necrotic, or Poison damage. The bonus equals your Intelligence modifier (minimum bonus of +1).	KEY:Alchemist ~ Alchemical Savant	DESC:Bonus +%1|max(INT,1)																									SORTKEY:Class_Artificer_01d1d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Restorative Reagents	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Artificer Class Feature.Class Feature.Alchemist.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can incorporate restorative reagents into some of your works, granting the following benefits: &nl; Fortify. Whenever a creature drinks an elixir you created with the Experimental Elixir feature, the creature gains Temporary Hit Points equal to your Intelligence modifier plus your Artificer level. Temporary HP: %1. &nl; Restore. You can cast Lesser Restoration without expending a spell slot and without preparing the spell, provided you use Alchemist's Supplies as the Spellcasting Focus. You can do so a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest. Times %1/day|RestorativeReagentsFortify|RestorativeReagentsRestoreTimes	KEY:Alchemist ~ Restorative Reagents				DEFINE:RestorativeReagentsFortify|0	DEFINE:RestorativeReagentsRestoreTimes|0				BONUS:VAR|RestorativeReagentsFortify|INT+ArtificerLVL	BONUS:VAR|RestorativeReagentsRestoreTimes|max(INT,1)																SORTKEY:Class_Artificer_01d1e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Chemical Mastery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Artificer Class Feature.Class Feature.Alchemist.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the following benefits: &nl; Alchemical Eruption. When you cast an Artificer spell that deals Acid, Fire, Necrotic, or Poison damage to a target, you can also deal 2d8 Force damage to that target. You can use this benefit only once on each of your turns. &nl; Chemical Resistance. You gain Resistance to Acid damage and Poison damage. &nl; Conjured Cauldron. You can cast Tasha's Bubbling Cauldron without expending a spell slot, without preparing the spell, and without Material components, provided you use Alchemist's Supplies as the Spellcasting Focus. Once you use this feature, you can�t use it again until you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Alchemist ~ Chemical Mastery																		SPELLS:Chemical Mastery|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=ArtificerLVL|Tasha's Bubling Cauldron								SORTKEY:Class_Artificer_01d1f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
